title: You Left Me Behind
info:
I got home late
And I found your note on the kitchen table
The writing so perfect
There's no sign of emotion
The words inside
Blurred from tears in my eyes
You said that were leaving
And you said that you'd tried

Oh why, did you have to leave
You might as well stick a knife in my heart
And leave me to die
Why did you have to leave
It feels like you've stabbed me in the heart
When you left me to die

Well there's nothing left to say
For too many things have already been said
And if I can't make you love me
Then I guess it has to end here
Gave no reasons, made no accusations
Don't know why you want to leave me
But it's too late to fight for you

Oh why [tell me why], did you have to leave
You might as well stick a knife in my heart
And leave me to die
Why [tell me why] did you have to leave
It feels like you've stabbed me in the heart
When you left me, you left me to die
